ers and ambitious artists.Through a mixture of memoir and interviews with well-known Mancunians such as Guy Garvey, Tunde Babalola, Sylvia Tella, Badly Drawn Boy and Stan Chow, David Scott portrays the city at the turn of the century in a way never seen before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aPopular musicxSocial aspectszEnglandzManchester. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / 21st Century.2bisacsh  a1990s.  a2000s.  aBritpop.  aIRA.  aManchester.  aNorth-west England.  adoves' badly drawn boy.  aelbow' i am kloot.  alocal history.  amanchester biography.  amanchester book.  amancunians.  amemoir.  amodern British history.  aoral history.  apopular culture.1 aScott, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152617225940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526172259423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526172259/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2023